1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 54-02 and a new section to
2 chapter 54-54 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to the designation of the state waltz
3 and state troubadour; and to provide for application.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 54-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 State waltz.
8 "Dancing Dakota", written and composed by Chuck Suchy, is the North Dakota state waltz.
9 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 54-54 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
10 and enacted as follows:
11 State troubadour.
12 The chairman of the North Dakota council on the arts shall designate an individual to serve
13 as the official state troubadour or trobairitz for a term of five years. The chairman may fill any
14 vacancy by appointment for the unexpired portion of the term vacated.
15 SECTION 3. APPLICATION. An official state troubadour must be appointed under section 2
16 of this Act at the conclusion of any term of the inaugural troubadour appointed by resolution by
17 the sixty-ninth legislative assembly.
